-- China Banks' Capital Adequacy Ratio Gains to 11%, CBRC's Liu Mingkang Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-26T00:58:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-26/china-banks-capital-adequacy-ratio-gains-to-11-cbrc-s-liu-mingkang-says.html

          
          
             China banks’ weighted average
capital adequacy ratio rose to 11.1 percent as of
March 31 from minus 2.98 percent in 2003, Liu Mingkang, chairman
of China Banking Regulatory Commission, said at a financial
forum in Shanghai today.  
 China banks’ bad loan coverage ratio was 170.2 percent at
the end of the first quarter, he said.   
          
          


  


        